SoundBox - Acknowledgments
==========================

This project would not be possible without the following open-source projects
and their contributors:

FFTW3 - Fastest Fourier Transform in the West
  Authors: Matteo Frigo and Steven G. Johnson
  Affiliation: Massachusetts Institute of Technology
  The auto-tune pitch correction feature is powered by FFTW3's high-performance
  FFT implementation. We gratefully acknowledge the exceptional work of the FFTW
  team in creating the fastest and most widely-used FFT library.
  https://www.fftw.org/
  License: GPL v2+

NAudio - .NET Audio Library
  Author: Mark Heath
  NAudio provides the audio capture and playback infrastructure that forms the
  backbone of SoundBox's audio pipeline.
  https://github.com/naudio/NAudio
  License: MIT

Microsoft Windows Driver Kit (WDK)
  The virtual audio device driver is built using Microsoft's PortCls framework
  and WDK toolchain.

We also thank the open-source audio processing community for the wealth of
knowledge on digital signal processing, phase vocoder techniques, and pitch
detection algorithms that informed this implementation.
